{"abstract":[{"text":"Learn how to cache products.","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/flare\/caching"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Flare\/documentation\/Flare"]]},"sections":[],"kind":"article","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Flare\/documentation\/Flare\/caching","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Caching products can improve the performance and user experience of your app by reducing the need to fetch product information from the App Store. In this guide, weâ€™ll explore how to cache products efficiently in your app."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Implementing Product Caching","level":2,"anchor":"Implementing-Product-Caching","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By default, Flare uses cached data if available; otherwise, it fetches the products. If you want to change this behavior, you need to configure Flare with a custom caching policy. For this, Flare provides two options "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Flare\/documentation\/Flare\/FetchCachePolicy\/fetch"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Flare\/documentation\/Flare\/FetchCachePolicy\/cachedOrFetch"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can override the default behaviour passing a ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Flare\/documentation\/Flare\/FetchCachePolicy\/fetch","type":"reference"},{"text":" with a configuration.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["Flare.default.configure(with: .init(Configuration(username: \"username\", fetchCachePolicy: .fetch)))"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This configuration tells Flare to always fetch the latest data, ignoring any cached data. You can adjust this behavior as needed for your app.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","title":"Caching Products","modules":[{"name":"Flare"}],"role":"article"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"references":{"doc://Flare/documentation/Flare":{"type":"topic","role":"collection","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Flare provides an elegant interface for In-App Purchases, supporting non-consumable and consumable purchases as well as subscriptions."}],"title":"Flare","identifier":"doc:\/\/Flare\/documentation\/Flare","url":"\/documentation\/flare","kind":"symbol"},"doc://Flare/documentation/Flare/FetchCachePolicy/fetch":{"type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Fetch the current data without using the cache."}],"url":"\/documentation\/flare\/fetchcachepolicy\/fetch","identifier":"doc:\/\/Flare\/documentation\/Flare\/FetchCachePolicy\/fetch","kind":"symbol","title":"FetchCachePolicy.fetch","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"case"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"fetch"}],"role":"symbol"},"doc://Flare/documentation/Flare/FetchCachePolicy/cachedOrFetch":{"fragments":[{"text":"case","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"cachedOrFetch","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"FetchCachePolicy.cachedOrFetch","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Use the cached data if available; otherwise, fetch the data.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Flare\/documentation\/Flare\/FetchCachePolicy\/cachedOrFetch","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/flare\/fetchcachepolicy\/cachedorfetch","role":"symbol"}}}